# Testing Rules

## TDD Cycle

```
RED → GREEN → REFACTOR
```

1. Write a failing test
2. Minimal implementation to pass
3. Improve the code

## Best Practices

- Test names describe behavior
- One assertion per test
- Arrange-Act-Assert pattern
- Test behavior, not implementation

## Test Naming

```javascript
// Good
it('should return empty array when no items match')
it('should throw error when input is invalid')

// Bad
it('test1')
it('works')
```

## Before Commit

```bash
npm test
npm run lint
npm run type-check
npm run build
```

## Before Push

```bash
npm test -- --coverage
npm run test:e2e
```

## Coverage Targets

| Type | Target |
|------|--------|
| Statements | 80% |
| Branches | 75% |
| Functions | 80% |
| Lines | 80% |
